Create KPIs and Slicer Visuals 12

Step 1. Create Average YOY Card Visual



Steps

  1. Click on empty space on the canvas and select the card visual from the Visualizations Pane
  2. Drag and drop Average YOY measure to the Value well under the Fields pane.
  3. Go to the Formatting tab select Percentage from Format drop down menu and set the decimal value to two.

Step 2. Format the Average YOY card visual

 Set the size and location of the visual


Steps

To adjust the size and location of the visual click on the visual, select the Format Pane and follow the steps below.

  1. Expand the General tab.
  2. Set the X Position to 534.
  3. Set the Y Position to 0.
  4. Set the Width to 198
  5. Set the Height to 144.

Step 3. Create Conditional Formatting for the card visual



Steps

This step is to format the font color for the visual. For negative figures the font should be green and for positive number the font should be red. 

  1. Select the card visual and then expand the Data Label in the Format Pane.
  2. Select the function (fx) button to open the color format dialogue box.
  3. Select the drop down menu on Format By tab and select Rules from the drop down list.
  4. Select the drop down menu on Based on Field and select the measure based on which to format the color. In our case we will select the .AverageYOY measure.
  5. Set the rules for color formatting and set Hexadecimal 1AAB40 for the first rule and Hexadecimal FF1500 for the second rule.
  6. Click on Ok button to close the dialogue box.

Step 4. Format the title font color and font size

     

Steps

We use the Format pane to format the visual

  1. Set the Category to Off.
  2. Set the Title to On and expand the Title option.
  3. Insert Average YOY  in to the Title Text box.
  4. Set the font color to white and set the background color to Hexadecimal 007FFF.
  5. Set the title alignment to center and text size to 18.

Step 5. Create the Number of Attack card visual


Steps

  1. Click on empty space on the canvas and select the card visual from the Visualizations Pane
  2. Drag and drop Total Shooting Measure into the Values well under Fields pane.
  3. Format the size and location of the visual by expanding the General tab under Format pane and entering the following values.

                    Set the X Position to 753.

                    Set the Y Position to 0.

                    Set the Width to 210.

                    Set the Height position to 144.


Step 6. Format the title of Number of Attacks Card Visual





    Step 7. Create Victims Per Shooting Card Visual


    Steps

    1. Click on empty space on the canvas and select the card visual from the Visualizations Pane.
    2. Drag and drop Victims Per shooting into the Values well under Fields pane.
    3. Format the size and location of the visual by expanding the General tab under Format pane and entering the following values.

                        Set the X Position to 983.

                        Set the Y Position to 0.

                        Set the Width to 221.

                        Set the Height position to 144.

    Step 8. Format the title of Victims Per Shooting card visual


    Step 9. Create the Year Slicer


    Steps

    1. Click on empty space on the canvas and select the Slicer visual from the Visualization Pane.
    2. Drag and drop the Year field into the values well under the Fields Pane
    3. To change the slicer into slider type, click on the drop down menu on the slicer and select the Between option.

    Step 10. Format the size and location of the slicer

    Steps

    To adjust the size and location of the visual click on the visual, select the Format Pane and follow the steps below.

    1. Expand the General tab.
    2. Set the X Position to 1225.
    3. Set the Y Position to 0.
    4. Set the Width to 258.
    5. Set the Height to 144.

    Step 11. Format the title of the slicer visual


    Steps

    We use the Format pane to format the visual

    1. Set the Slicer Header to Off.
    2. Set the Title to On and expand the Title option.
    3. Insert Year into the title Text Box.
    4. Set the font color to white and set the background color to Hexadecimal 007FFF.
    5. Set the title alignment to center and text size to 18.

    Step 12. Turn the visual shadow ON


    Steps

    In this step we will turn the visual shadow on to make it standout against the background.

    1. Click on the Visual.
    2. Go to Format Pane and turn the shadow on as shown in the image above.

    The below link provides explanation on how to use card visualization in Power BI.

    https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pe6Y6GVhHPw
